parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine cooling fan can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to a potential fire, which can increase the risk of injury to occupants and persons outside the vehicle, as well as property damage.
symptoms: The radiator fan makes a sound
followed by a burning smell
the vehicle overheats
the fan stops working
and the vehicle goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning indicators to illuminate, the vehicle to slow down, and the engine to stall, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Various warning indicators illuminate
the vehicle slows down
the engine stalls
and the vehicle is unable to accelerate beyond a certain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the TPMS can cause the system to provide unreliable information, which can lead to accidents or property damage due to underinflated tires.
symptoms: The TPMS light comes on intermittently
the system provides unreliable information
and the light stays on despite proper tire pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Various electrical systems malfunction
and the dealer is unable to diagnose or repair the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the display to provide incorrect information, which can lead to accidents or property damage due to driver confusion.
symptoms: The display provides incorrect information
and different functions cannot be set.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission mount can cause the engine and transmission to drop, leading to a loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges forward
the engine and transmission drop
the vehicle goes out of gear
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or go out of gear, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle goes into limp mode
the vehicle stalls
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the vehicle shifts into neutral
the transmission clunks loudly
the vehicle loses engine power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cooling system can cause the engine to overheat, leading to potential engine damage and accidents.
symptoms: The radiator cooling fan stops working
the vehicle overheats
the fuses for the fan blow.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: An abnormal noise emits from the rear driver-side brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to engage or release
the parking brake cables freeze in the winter
the parking brake shoes wear down excessively
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked on an incline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes lock up
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes make an abnormal noise
the rotors need to be turned frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The emergency brake engages unexpectedly while driving
the emergency brake fails to release
the vehicle stops suddenly while driving.
